<plot>Desert Rose: an investigative documentary measuring the life path of a once FBI Most Wanted fugitive. Theresa "Rose" Grosso received her Most Wanted status after her fourth escape from prison. In 1969, Theresa Grosso was convicted of allegedly murdering Melvin Lukart in cold blood. Her identical twin sister testified that Theresa gunned down the man when they were out partying. The gun was the twin's property, and Theresa still claims that she doesn't remember the incident. Based on the circumstances of Theresa's case, James seeks the truth and begins to make sense of the years Theresa spent on the lam.</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?141733</url></doc>
